Jury Welcome
9/29/2015 Trial     Upon no response from plaintiff,  paper and physical exhibits destroyed as of 10/16/2019.

Atty. Jeffrey Sisley appears for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant appears in custody and by Atty. Matt Last. Counsel prepared to proceed to trial today. Recess. 
  9:25 am   Jurors reported and given oath.
  9:26 am   20 jurors called to jury box.
  9:30 am   Court voir dire of jurors.
  9:47 am   Atty. Sisley voir dire of jurors.
10:00 am   Atty. Last voir dire of jurors.
10:15 am   Counsel striking of jurors.
10:20 am   12 jurors called to hear case and given oath.
10:24 am   Court preliminary instructions to jury.
10:26 am   Court/jury recess.
10:45 am   Court orders sequestration of witnesses.
10:46 am   Opening statement by Atty. Sisley.
10:58 am   Opening statement by Atty. Last.
11:08 am   Deputy M. Halverson sworn and testified. Exam by Atty. Sisley.
11:57 am   Lunch recess to 1:15 pm.
  1:28 pm   Deputy M. Halverson resumes stand. Crossexam by Atty. Last, redirect, recross.
  2:08 pm   N.R. sworn and testified. Exam by Atty. Sisley.
  2:48 pm   State Rests.
  2:49 pm   Jury excused/Court recess.
  3:08 pm   Court colloquy with defendant. Court accepts that defendant does not wish to testify. 
                    Atty. Last motion to dismiss. Court denies motion.
  3:12 pm   Jury in Court. Defense rests.
  3:13 pm   Closing statement by Atty. Sisley.
  3:24 pm   Closing statement by Atty. Last.
  3:42 pm   Rebuttal statement by Atty. Sisley.
  3:44 pm   Court instructs jury.
  3:55 pm   Bailiff sworn.
  3:56 pm   Jury leaves for deliberation. 
  4:28 pm   Court is informed jury has reached a verdict.
  4:40 pm   Court/counsel/defendant/jury present. Verdict read: Guilty
  4:42 pm   Jury polled, thanked and excused. 
  4:44 pm   DA motion for judgment on the verdict. Defense motion for judgment notwithstanding the verdict. Court grants motion for judgment on the verdict.
                    Court remands defendant forthwith to the custody of the Ozaukee County Sheriff's Dept. Sentencing set for 10/7/2015 at 2:00 pm.
